Generate MCPServer YAML manifests from .mcp metadata. Normal user deploys should use server deploy directly; this command is for review, GitOps, and admin workflows that need YAML output.

Usage:
  mcp-runtime server generate [flags]

Flags:
  -h, --help                   help for generate
      --metadata-dir string    Directory containing .mcp metadata files (default ".mcp")
      --metadata-file string   Path to .mcp metadata file
      --output string          Output directory for generated MCPServer manifests (default "manifests")

Global Flags:
      --debug      Enable debug mode with structured error logging
      --use-kube   Use direct Kubernetes mode with kubectl; requires admin/operator cluster access (admin/dev/test only)
